<h1>Wingspan S.T.E.A.M Camp</h1>
<!--Mission Statement -->

<h2>Get ready for your child/children to have a fun-filled, brain-building week of science, technology, engineering, art, and math activities.</h2>

<p>All proceeds go towards Viera Hawk Robotics team expenses such as travel to competitions, robot parts, and new equipment.</p>

<p>FRC Wingspan #7431 student team members will be serving as our camp counselors under the supervision of two BPS teachers/Hawk Robotics lead mentors, Mr. Dave Formanek and Mrs. Kim Beiderman.&nbsp;</p>

<h3><strong>Pertinent Information:</strong></h3>

<h4><strong>Who</strong>: Children in grades K-8.</h4>

<p><em>Only 30 slots, first come, first serve. We will create a wait list when we reach max 30.</em></p>

<h4><strong>When</strong>: June 26 through June 30&nbsp;</h4>

<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; 9:00-3:00</p>

<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Extended Day available 7:30-9:00, 3:00-6:00 [$10 an hour; half-hour increments]</p>

<h4><strong>Where</strong>: Viera High School</h4>

<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;6103 Stadium Pkwy, Melbourne, FL 32940</p>

<p>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; Room 4-113</p>

<h4><strong>What</strong>: Example activities your child will be participating in are: low-tech coding, design your own obstacle course, Oobleck egg drop challenge, circuit crafts, candy DNA, math games, scavenger hunts and tons MORE!&nbsp; Indoor and outdoor, rain or shine!</h4>

<p style="text-align:center">Camp T-shirts! Snacks! Friday Pizza Party!</p>

<p style="text-align:center"><em>Lunch not provided, please pack a lunch.&nbsp;</em></p>

<h4><strong>How much</strong>: <strong>$349 per child,</strong> 10% sibling discount available</h4>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;PayPal payments, click here&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;Cash or checks made out to The Maker Effect Foundation MEMO: Wingspan 7431</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">Sent via mail to&nbsp;8600 Commodity Cir #158, Orlando, FL 32819&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>

<p style="margin-left:40px">&nbsp;or given to the Viera High School front office c/o David Formanek</p>

<p>Please complete the registration form below. <strong>One per family.</strong></p>

